# NOTE: Keep this list short (~8 entries). Remove old ones as new ones land.
CHANGELOG = [
    "Quick Cast: INT-scaled skip-the-channel-init-swing for casters (build 402). Death diagnostic on b401 F25 caster failures revealed the F25 wall isn't 1-shot kills (0/30 across elf+human) -- it's cast-turn attrition: 15/30 elf deaths and 13/30 human deaths happened in spell_casting_mode. Each L2-L3 spell channels 1 turn before firing, and the monster swings during the channel-init turn (~80-90 raw at F25) AND again after the spell fires. A 3-spell sequence (Stone Skin -> Mass Heal -> Flame Lance) burns 240-270 raw dmg taken across 6 monster swings against monsters the caster can't kill in time. New caster identity feature: high-INT casters roll (INT - 17) * 4% chance per L2+ cast to skip the channel-init monster swing -- 'arcane reflexes finish the spell instantly'. Capped at 50%. Curve: INT 18 -> 4%, INT 20 -> 12%, INT 22 -> 20%, INT 25 -> 32%, INT 28 -> 44%, INT 30+ -> 50%. The channel-complete swing (after spell fires) is intentionally left intact so the monster still gets a counter-action -- quick-cast only buys back the channeling 'lock-in' period, not the whole exchange. Tracks via gs.game_stats.quick_casts. Smoke test on seed 42 F25 elf: 3 quick-casts out of 4 spells cast (high variance on small sample, expected 32%). Saves ~80 raw dmg per quick-cast trigger.",
    "Short-fight-prey filter on Stone Skin buff (build 401). The b400 audit showed F25 elf spending 78% of cast budget on defense (Stone Skin 26) vs offense (Flame Lance 8). The m_level >= pc_level - 1 gate fired on every parity-level fight, including against small-HP enemies that would die in 1-2 alpha-strikes regardless of Stone Skin -- the 18 MP + 1-turn buff cost never paid back on those. Added a second gate: m_max_hp >= pc_max_hp * 0.30, filtering out short-fight prey while still triggering on the long-fight bosses where Stone Skin's 4-turn +8 DEF window pays back. Brief detour through an hp_pct < 0.75 gate (defer buff until already-hurt) regressed F15 elf 6/30 -> 1/30 because the elf took the big hit BEFORE the buff fired -- preemptive on turn 1 was correct; the over-firing fix is the prey filter, not deferral. F15 elf Stone Skin trigger now skips fights against weak ~50-HP monsters that the elf one-shots with Lightning Bolt at INT 19 (58 dmg after b400 scaling), preserving the buff investment for fights that last 3+ turns.",
    "Additive INT-scaling layer on spell damage / healing (build 400). The b399 caster sweep showed mana regen alone didn't move F20-F25 caster survival -- elf 0/30 at F25 even with full-cast budget. Audit traced it to spell damage staying flat across stat investment on low-tier spells: Mind Touch (L0) at INT 25 only hit for 18 vs 12 at INT 12 because the existing int_bonus formula's per-level multiplier (`max(0, INT-10) * spell.level // 3`) gave nothing to L0 cantrips. A cantrip-only caster (e.g. F15 human Mind Touch) got zero scaling reward for the b397 elixir-pad INT investment. Added a flat `max(0, (INT-15)//2)` bonus on top of the existing per-level scaling, applied in both spell-cast paths -- combat.py:_execute_charged_spell and characters.py:Character.cast_spell. Damage at INT 25: Mind Touch 18 -> 23 (+28%), Lightning Bolt 53 -> 58 (+9%), Flame Lance 55 -> 60 (+9%). Healing at INT 25: Mass Heal 72 -> 77 HP. The scaling is intentionally modest on high-level spells (already over-scaled by int_bonus) but meaningful on L0-L1 spells where the prior formula's level multiplier was 0-1. Side benefit: F15 human cantrip-only casters now see Mind Touch climb 6 -> 13 dmg (INT 16, no int_bonus contribution from L0 spells), making cantrips a real combat option instead of strictly worse than melee swings at L13.",
    "Race + INT-scaled mana regen for caster identity (build 399). The b398 spell pick + Stone Skin fixes lifted F15 caster survival 3-4x (elf 5% -> 23%, human 8% -> 30%), but F20-F25 casters still cratered (elf 7% / 0%, human 7% / 0%). The b398 audit showed casters were getting 65 MP/fight worth of value out of their spellbook -- Stone Skin 18 + Flame Lance 17 + Mass Heal 30 -- but the uniform 1 MP / 5 moves regen rate replenished only 3 MP across a typical 15-move room transit, so the second fight could only afford one spell instead of three. Rewrote process_mana_regen in items.py with race-flavored tick intervals and an INT-scaled per-tick gain. New curve: elf 1 tick / 2 moves, human 1 tick / 3 moves, dwarf 1 tick / 5 moves (unchanged -- magic is hard for them); per-tick MP = 1 + (INT - 16) // 4 so a high-INT caster scales gain alongside cost. Effective rates: F15 elf (INT ~19) 50 MP/100 moves, F25 elf (INT ~25) 150 MP/100 moves (vs 20 MP/100 moves pre-b399 for everyone). The F25 elf's 237 max_mana now fully regenerates across ~160 moves of exploration -- sustainable across a long session instead of decaying to zero by mid-run. Dwarf regen unchanged because they're not the caster race; their identity is HP-tank, not mana-throughput. F20 elf cast rate jumped 63% -> 77% in the audit and F25 elf 57% -> 65% -- they're now casting through fights instead of stretching mana between them. Combined with the b397 stat-elixir pad + b398 power-aware spell pick, this should close the elf/human survival gap at F20+ vs the dwarf martial baseline.",
    "Smart spell-pick + pre-fight Stone Skin + expanded F<N> spellbook (build 398). The b397 plants now arrive at depth with a stocked spellbook, but the b397 spell audit revealed the smart-policy was wasting it. (1) Spell pick is now power-aware: pre-b398 `spell_casting_mode` used `rng.choice(affordable_dmg)` which gave 6-dmg Mind Touch the same probability as 31-dmg Lightning Bolt -- F25 elf cast Lightning Bolt 5/108 times (4.6%) and Mind Touch ~70% of the time. Damage pick is now `max(affordable_dmg, key=base_power)` -- strongest spell that fits mana. Heal pick is now `smallest heal >= deficit` (fallback to largest affordable) so a F25 elf with Mass Heal in book doesn't spam +15 Minor Heal at 30% HP when +60 Mass Heal is the right call. (2) Mind Touch / weak cantrips excluded from `affordable_dmg`: anything below base_power 10 falls out, so the F15 human with only Mind Touch (6 dmg) now defaults to melee `a` (weapon hits for 12-20 at L13) instead of spamming the cantrip 538 times across an 8-seed audit. Cantrips still available via `affordable_spells` if no real spell is affordable. (3) Pre-fight Stone Skin buff: combat_mode now fires `c` on turn 1 of any parity-or-tougher fight (m_level >= pc_level - 1) when `defense_boost` isn't already active, and spell_casting_mode picks Stone Skin first. Battle Hymn intentionally NOT auto-cast -- audit on rc1 showed back-to-back buff turns (Stone Skin -> Battle Hymn) ate 2/3 of the typical fight, netting 1 buffed damage cast at 36 MP cost. Stone Skin alone pays back even on 2-turn fights because +8 DEF cuts incoming damage immediately. (4) Expanded spell tier list with damage variety + buffs + status cure: F13+ Fireball (L1, 20 dmg fire), F15+ Lightning Bolt (L2, 31 dmg wind), F16+ Battle Hymn (L2, +10 ATK buff), F19+ Purify (L1, cure poison), F20+ Flame Lance (L2, 33 dmg fire), plus Greater Heal / Mass Heal in the heal ladder. F15 elf now carries 6-7 memorized spells; F25 elf carries up to 11 spells / 23 slots used of 24 max. (5) memorized_spells obs now exposes `base_power` so the policy can score picks. Audit after b398: F15 elf cast distribution went from {Mind Touch 97, Minor Heal 71, Ice Shard 51, Lightning Bolt 30} to {Lightning Bolt 98, Ice Shard 22, Heal 15, Fireball 13, Minor Heal 6} -- Mind Touch usage eliminated, Lightning Bolt 3.3x more frequent. F25 elf went from {Minor Heal 71, Lightning Bolt 5} to {Mass Heal 30, Flame Lance 23} -- right-sized heals and strongest damage spell.",
    "Stat-elixir pad + pre-memorized utility spells for F<N> plants (build 397). The b396 inventory grants closed the consumables gap but the stat profile + spellbook were still underbaked: F15 humans/dwarves had no permanent stat elixirs (despite real F15 survivors typically finding 2-3), and elves at F10+ had memorized only the Mind Touch cantrip from the starter pack. Two coordinated changes in playtest_harness.py:_plant_survivor_baseline. (1) Permanent stat-elixir pad: +1 to each of STR / DEX / INT per 5 floors of depth (F5 -> +1, F10 -> +2, F15 -> +3, F20 -> +4, F25 -> +5). Stacked equally across stats because elixirs are race-agnostic drops. Pushes F20+ humans into casting range (default INT 10 + 3 race-bias + 4 elixir = 17), keeps F15- humans non-casting (matches the human-as-late-bloomer archetype), and gives all races meaningful late-game scaling beyond level-based unspent_stat_points. F15 elf jumps from INT 16 to INT 19 (slot capacity 9 -> 11), F15 dwarf STR 16 -> 19 (more raw combat). (2) Pre-memorized utility spells via new _grant_memorized_spells helper: tier list scaling with depth -- F5+ Minor Heal (Lv0), F8+ Heal (Lv1), F10+ Ice Shard (Lv0), F12+ Stone Skin (Lv2 defense), F15+ Lightning Bolt (Lv2 damage), F18+ Greater Heal (Lv2), F22+ Mass Heal (Lv3). Each spell is added only if the planted character has slot capacity (get_max_memorized_spell_slots) for it, so dwarves and low-INT humans skip cleanly. Verified profile: F15 elf carries Minor Heal + Heal + Ice Shard + Stone Skin + Lightning Bolt + cantrips (8/11 slots used); F20 human / elf both carry 6 memorized spells (10/14 and 10/17 slots used); F25 elf has the full caster build (Mass Heal at 13/24 slots). Combined with b396's stat-derived HP/MP recompute, F15 elf goes from 148/110 HP/MP to 154/119, F20 elf from 198/166 to 206/178. The buff is calibrated to mirror what a real F<N> survivor would have accumulated, not to make plants invincible.",
    "Survivor inventory grants for F<N> plants + vendor identify oscillation fix + non-game_loop wedge escape (build 396). Three coordinated changes. (1) `_grant_survivor_inventory` in playtest_harness.py: scales an items pack with start_floor to mirror what a real F<N> player would have looted / bought across the F1..F<N-1> stretch. F1+ always gets Cooking Kit (addresses the 12/90 starvation deaths in the b394 F15-plant sweep -- Cooking Kit was pulled from starter pack in b358 to make F3 cooking a real decision, but a F15 survivor would have one by now). F5+: 3 Healing Potions, 2 Scroll of Identify, +3 Lantern Fuel cans. F8+: Curing Kit, 2 Greater Healing Pots, Mapping scroll, 3 Mana Potions, +2 Fuel. F12+: 2 Superior Healing Pots, 2 Scroll of Protection, 2 pre-crafted Bratwurst sausages. F15+: 2 Master Healing Pots, Scroll of Restoration, Scroll of Teleportation, +2 Fuel. F20+: +2 Master Healing Pots, +2 Mapping, +2 Protection. F15-plant agent now carries ~1060 HP of healing budget on top of full 154 max HP, comparable to a player who survived to F15 organically. (2) Vendor-shop identify policy oscillation fix in smart_policy: prior gate `obs.last_action != proposed` only blocked the SAME slot from immediate repeat, so with 2+ unidentified items the loop oscillated id4 <-> id5 indefinitely (b395 seed=223 dwarf F13 burned 900+ turns alternating two scroll identify attempts). Tightened to `last_action.startswith('id')` -- any prior id<N> means we've already tried identifying THIS vendor visit and should leave. (3) Non-game_loop wedge escape: the b395 wedge break only fired in movement modes (game_loop, stairs_up_mode, stairs_down_mode); the vendor_shop identify wedge slipped through. Extended the wedge break to ALL modes -- when freeze_streak >= 30 in a non-movement mode, force 'x' (back) to drop the agent into game_loop where the wayfinder can re-evaluate. 'x' is the standard cancel/leave key across most modes; if a mode doesn't accept it the dispatch falls through harmlessly. Mini-sweep verification (30 seeds x 3 races x 1500T F15-plant): pre-b395 9/90 wedged; b395 wedge-only fix had 2/90 unresolved freezes; b396 has 0/90 wedge-break fires, 0/90 max_osc >= 100, 0/90 max_freeze >= 50. Mean moves 391/run, mean deepest F16.7, max F22.",
    "Smart-policy wedge break for freeze + persistent oscillation loops (build 395). The b394 F15-plant sweep surfaced a long-tail smart-policy bug: 9/90 runs wedged 500-2200 turns burning the whole 2500T budget on period-1 'l' (lantern) loops or period-2 'wn'/'ew'/'sn' direction loops the existing recent_step_set + swap-if-backtrack + stairs_up 'u' valve could not resolve. Two reproducible cases isolated: (a) seed=7 elf F15-plant T119 -- pc in a corridor with N/E=walls, S=monster (avoided when weak), W=floor; the wayfinder targets a feature east, _swap_if_backtrack returns 'e' because 'e' (a wall) isn't in recent_step_set (which tracks tile positions, not wall-bounces), 'e' fails, agent backtracks 'w', repeat. (b) seed=13 human F16 T282 -- pc landed on U at (1,1) with only S walkable; U is explicitly EXCLUDED from visited_features (the line 2479 carve-out -- 'we want the wayfinder to re-target stairs for retreat'), so after stepping S, the BFS retargets U from (1,2), the agent steps N back onto U, oscillation. Two harness changes in playtest_harness.py: (1) Freeze detector: every step() now compares (z, x, y, hp, kills_on_floor) to the prior step; identical = freeze_streak++, else reset to 0. Exposed in obs as `freeze_streak`. Catches pure tile-freezing (the lantern wedge keeps pc.xy static because 'l' doesn't tick a game turn for hunger/spawns). (2) Wedge-break at top of smart_policy: when freeze_streak >= 30 in any movement-capable mode OR oscillation.streak >= 60 in game_loop, override the policy's next action with a random walkable, non-blocked, non-recent cardinal direction. Three-tier fallback: tier 1 picks from non-recent walkable; tier 2 allows recent (escape > anti-backtrack); tier 3 returns 'pass' to advance world state if completely cornered. Mini-sweep verification: 90 runs (30 seeds x 3 races x 1500T F15-plant) -- pre-fix: 9/90 wedged; post-fix: 2/90 fired the wedge break and resolved cleanly, 0/90 unresolved oscillation, 0/90 frozen >50T, 0/90 low-moves stuck. Mean moves 373/run (vs ~0 for wedged pre-fix runs). Thresholds chosen above the existing valves (oscillation 60 > stairs_up 50, freeze 30 > typical mid-mode multi-turn handlers like chest open / pool drink) to avoid false-positives on legitimate multi-turn interactions.",
]
